{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm Michael Shermer,\ndirector of the Skeptics Society,"},{"time":2556,"text":"publisher of \"Skeptic\" magazine."},{"time":4112,"text":"We investigate claims of the paranormal,"},{"time":6049,"text":"pseudo-science, fringe groups and cults,\nand claims of all kinds between,"},{"time":9755,"text":"science and pseudo-science\nand non-science and junk science,"},{"time":12673,"text":"voodoo science, pathological science,\nbad science, non-science,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and plain old non-sense."},{"time":17911,"text":"And unless you've been on Mars recently,"},{"time":19852,"text":"you know there's a lot of that out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21894,"text":"Some people call us debunkers,\nwhich is kind of a negative term."},{"time":24940,"text":"But let's face it, there's a lot of bunk."},{"time":27072,"text":"We are like the bunko squads\nof the police departments out there --"},{"time":30549,"text":"well, we're sort of like\nthe Ralph Naders of bad ideas,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":34000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":35254,"text":"trying to replace bad ideas\nwith good ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"I'll show you an example of a bad idea."},{"time":39887,"text":"I brought this with me,"},{"time":41069,"text":"this was given to us\nby NBC Dateline to test."},{"time":45000,"text":"It's produced by the Quadro\nCorporation of West Virginia."},{"time":48310,"text":"It's called the Quadro 2000 Dowser Rod."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51244,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":52714,"text":"This was being sold to high-school\nadministrators for $900 apiece."},{"time":58000,"text":"It's a piece of plastic with a Radio\nShack antenna attached to it."},{"time":62351,"text":"You could dowse for all sorts of things,"},{"time":64341,"text":"but this particular one was built\nto dowse for marijuana"},{"time":67758,"text":"in students' lockers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":71484,"text":"So the way it works\nis you go down the hallway,"},{"time":75053,"text":"and you see if it tilts\ntoward a particular locker,"},{"time":78076,"text":"and then you open the locker."},{"time":79544,"text":"So it looks something like this."},{"time":81145,"text":"I'll show you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83809,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"Well, it has kind of a right-leaning bias."},{"time":88415,"text":"Well, this is science,\nso we'll do a controlled experiment."},{"time":91244,"text":"It'll go this way for sure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92850,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":96808,"text":"Sir, do you want to empty\nyour pockets, please, sir?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":99358,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":101220,"text":"So the question was, can it actually\nfind marijuana in students' lockers?"},{"time":104701,"text":"And the answer is,\nif you open enough of them, yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107323,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108370,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":110000,"text":"But in science, we have to keep track\nof the misses, not just the hits."},{"time":113405,"text":"And that's probably the key lesson\nto my short talk here:"},{"time":116695,"text":"This is how psychics work, astrologers,\ntarot card readers and so on."},{"time":120453,"text":"People remember the hits\nand forget the misses."},{"time":122696,"text":"In science, we keep the whole database,"},{"time":124615,"text":"and look to see if the number\nof hits somehow stands out"},{"time":127300,"text":"from the total number\nyou'd expect by chance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129537,"text":"In this case, we tested it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130855,"text":"We had two opaque boxes:"},{"time":132371,"text":"one with government-approved THC\nmarijuana, and one with nothing."},{"time":136029,"text":"And it got it 50 percent of the time --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":137934,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":139051,"text":"which is exactly what you'd expect\nwith a coin-flip model."},{"time":142000,"text":"So that's just a fun little example\nhere of the sorts of things we do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146015,"text":"\"Skeptic\" is the quarterly publication.\nEach one has a particular theme."},{"time":149507,"text":"This one is on the future of intelligence."},{"time":151605,"text":"Are people getting smarter or dumber?"},{"time":153400,"text":"I have an opinion of this myself\nbecause of the business I'm in,"},{"time":156472,"text":"but in fact, people, it turns out,\nare getting smarter."},{"time":159163,"text":"Three IQ points per 10 years, going up."},{"time":162000,"text":"Sort of an interesting thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163675,"text":"With science, don't think of skepticism\nas a thing, or science as a thing."},{"time":167246,"text":"Are science and religion compatible?"},{"time":169000,"text":"It's like, are science\nand plumbing compatible?"},{"time":171255,"text":"They're just two different things."},{"time":172913,"text":"Science is not a thing. It's a verb."},{"time":174676,"text":"It's a way of thinking about things."},{"time":176422,"text":"It's a way of looking for natural\nexplanations for all phenomena."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179516,"text":"I mean, what's more likely:"},{"time":180890,"text":"that extraterrestrial intelligences\nor multi-dimensional beings"},{"time":184477,"text":"travel across vast distances\nof interstellar space"},{"time":186891,"text":"to leave a crop circle in Farmer Bob's\nfield in Puckerbrush, Kansas"},{"time":190095,"text":"to promote skeptic.com, our web page?"},{"time":191929,"text":"Or is it more likely that a reader\nof \"Skeptic\" did this with Photoshop?"},{"time":196431,"text":"And in all cases we have to ask --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":198105,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":199953,"text":"What's the more likely explanation?"},{"time":202000,"text":"Before we say something\nis out of this world,"},{"time":204191,"text":"we should first make sure\nthat it's not in this world."},{"time":206879,"text":"What's more likely:"},{"time":208054,"text":"that Arnold had extraterrestrial help\nin his run for the governorship,"},{"time":211404,"text":"or that the \"World Weekly News\"\nmakes stuff up?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":213926,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215339,"text":"The same theme is expressed nicely\nhere in this Sidney Harris cartoon."},{"time":220025,"text":"For those of you in the back,\nit says here: \"Then a miracle occurs."},{"time":223264,"text":"I think you need to be more\nexplicit here in step two.\""},{"time":226000,"text":"This single slide completely dismantles\nthe intelligent design arguments."},{"time":230520,"text":"There's nothing more to it than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232392,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":233466,"text":"You can say a miracle occurs,"},{"time":234878,"text":"it's just that it doesn't explain\nanything or offer anything."},{"time":237868,"text":"There's nothing to test."},{"time":239042,"text":"It's the end of the conversation\nfor intelligent design creationists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242514,"text":"And it's true, scientists sometimes throw\nterms out as linguistic place fillers --"},{"time":247424,"text":"dark energy or dark matter,\nsomething like that --"},{"time":249796,"text":"until we figure out what it is,\nwe'll call it this."},{"time":252280,"text":"It's the beginning of the causal\nchain for science."},{"time":255005,"text":"For intelligent design creationists,\nit's the end of the chain."},{"time":259104,"text":"So again, we can ask this:\nwhat's more likely?"},{"time":261300,"text":"Are UFOs alien spaceships, or perceptual\ncognitive mistakes, or even fakes?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265715,"text":"This is a UFO shot from my house\nin Altadena, California,"},{"time":269000,"text":"looking down over Pasadena."},{"time":271000,"text":"And if it looks a lot like a Buick\nhubcap, it's because it is."},{"time":274545,"text":"You don't even need Photoshop\nor high-tech equipment,"},{"time":277307,"text":"you don't need computers."},{"time":278529,"text":"This was shot with a throwaway\nKodak Instamatic camera."},{"time":282000,"text":"You just have somebody off on the side\nwith a hubcap ready to go."},{"time":285120,"text":"Camera's ready -- that's it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287042,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":288503,"text":"So, although it's possible\nthat most of these things are fake"},{"time":292000,"text":"or illusions or so on,\nand that some of them are real,"},{"time":295738,"text":"it's more likely that all of them\nare fake, like the crop circles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298895,"text":"On a more serious note, in all of science\nwe're looking for a balance"},{"time":302300,"text":"between data and theory."},{"time":304000,"text":"In the case of Galileo,\nhe had two problems"},{"time":308000,"text":"when he turned his telescope to Saturn."},{"time":310385,"text":"First of all, there was no\ntheory of planetary rings."},{"time":313531,"text":"Second of all, his data\nwas grainy and fuzzy,"},{"time":315748,"text":"and he couldn't quite make out\nwhat he was looking at."},{"time":318300,"text":"So he wrote that he had seen --"},{"time":320000,"text":"\"I have observed that the furthest\nplanet has three bodies.\""},{"time":323531,"text":"And this is what he ended up\nconcluding that he saw."},{"time":326420,"text":"So without a theory of planetary\nrings and with only grainy data,"},{"time":330000,"text":"you can't have a good theory."},{"time":331942,"text":"It wasn't solved until 1655."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333585,"text":"This is Christiaan Huygens's book\nthat catalogs all the mistakes"},{"time":336623,"text":"people made trying to figure out\nwhat was going on with Saturn."},{"time":339609,"text":"It wasn't till Huygens had two things:"},{"time":341489,"text":"He had a good theory of planetary rings\nand how the solar system operated,"},{"time":345999,"text":"and he had better telescopic,\nmore fine-grain data"},{"time":348886,"text":"in which he could figure out that\nas the Earth is going around faster --"},{"time":352453,"text":"according to Kepler's Laws --\nthan Saturn, then we catch up with it."},{"time":355705,"text":"And we see the angles of the rings\nat different angles, there."},{"time":359000,"text":"And that, in fact, turns out to be true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361244,"text":"The problem with having a theory is that\nit may be loaded with cognitive biases."},{"time":366565,"text":"So one of the problems of explaining\nwhy people believe weird things"},{"time":369856,"text":"is that we have things, on a simple level,"},{"time":371948,"text":"and then I'll go to more serious ones."},{"time":373800,"text":"Like, we have a tendency to see faces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375700,"text":"This is the face on Mars."},{"time":377500,"text":"In 1976, where there was a whole movement\nto get NASA to photograph that area"},{"time":382036,"text":"because people thought this was monumental\narchitecture made by Martians."},{"time":385976,"text":"Here's the close-up of it from 2001."},{"time":388771,"text":"If you squint, you can still see the face."},{"time":391255,"text":"And when you're squinting,"},{"time":392581,"text":"you're turning that from fine-grain\nto coarse-grain,"},{"time":395628,"text":"so you're reducing\nthe quality of your data."},{"time":397939,"text":"And if I didn't tell you what to look for,\nyou'd still see the face,"},{"time":401192,"text":"because we're programmed\nby evolution to see faces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403645,"text":"Faces are important for us socially."},{"time":405820,"text":"And of course, happy faces,\nfaces of all kinds are easy to see."},{"time":409312,"text":"You see the happy face on Mars, there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411232,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412407,"text":"If astronomers were frogs,\nperhaps they'd see Kermit the Frog."},{"time":415344,"text":"Do you see him there? Little froggy legs."},{"time":417688,"text":"Or if geologists were elephants?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":420736,"text":"Religious iconography."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":426825,"text":"Discovered by a Tennessee baker in 1996."},{"time":429000,"text":"He charged five bucks a head\nto come see the nun bun"},{"time":431501,"text":"till he got a cease-and-desist\nfrom Mother Teresa's lawyer."},{"time":435238,"text":"Here's Our Lady of Guadalupe and Our\nLady of Watsonville, just down the street,"},{"time":439000,"text":"or is it up the street from here?"},{"time":440628,"text":"Tree bark is particularly good\nbecause it's nice and grainy, branchy,"},{"time":444000,"text":"black-and-white splotchy and you can\nget the pattern-seeking --"},{"time":447024,"text":"humans are pattern-seeking animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"Here's the Virgin Mary on the side\nof a glass window in Sao Paulo."},{"time":452587,"text":"Here's when the Virgin Mary made\nher appearance on a cheese sandwich --"},{"time":456025,"text":"which I got to actually\nhold in a Las Vegas casino --"},{"time":458539,"text":"of course, this being America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460100,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":461649,"text":"This casino paid $28,500\non eBay for the cheese sandwich."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":468000,"text":"But who does it really look like?\nThe Virgin Mary?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":470405,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":472408,"text":"It has that sort of\npuckered lips, 1940s-era look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476297,"text":"Virgin Mary in Clearwater, Florida."},{"time":478000,"text":"I actually went to see this one."},{"time":480000,"text":"There was a lot of people there."},{"time":481858,"text":"The faithful come in their wheelchairs\nand crutches, and so on."},{"time":486534,"text":"We went down and investigated."},{"time":488419,"text":"Just to give you a size, that's Dawkins,\nme and The Amazing Randi,"},{"time":491616,"text":"next to this two,\ntwo and a half story-sized image."},{"time":494053,"text":"All these candles, thousands of candles\npeople had lit in tribute to this."},{"time":497579,"text":"So we walked around the backside,\nto see what was going on."},{"time":500408,"text":"It turns out wherever there's\na sprinkler head and a palm tree,"},{"time":503763,"text":"you get the effect."},{"time":505000,"text":"Here's the Virgin Mary on the backside,\nwhich they started to wipe off."},{"time":508405,"text":"I guess you can only have\none miracle per building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514357,"text":"So is it really a miracle of Mary,\nor is it a miracle of Marge?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":518060,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":519085,"text":"And now I'm going to finish up\nwith another example of this,"},{"time":522712,"text":"with auditory illusions."},{"time":525513,"text":"There's this film, \"White Noise,\"\nwith Michael Keaton,"},{"time":528063,"text":"about the dead talking back to us."},{"time":530621,"text":"By the way, the whole business of talking\nto the dead is not that big a deal."},{"time":534310,"text":"Anybody can do it, turns out."},{"time":535819,"text":"It's getting the dead to talk\nback that's the really hard part."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538931,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":540053,"text":"In this case, supposedly, these messages\nare hidden in electronic phenomena."},{"time":543859,"text":"There's a ReverseSpeech.com web page\nwhere I downloaded this stuff."},{"time":547168,"text":"This is the most famous one\nof all of these."},{"time":550343,"text":"Here's the forward version\nof the very famous song."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553168,"text":"(Music with lyrics)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":554263,"text":"If there's a bustle in your hedgerow\ndon't be alarmed now."},{"time":560089,"text":"It's just a spring clean\nfor the May Queen."},{"time":565764,"text":"Yes, there are two paths you\ncan go by, but in the long run,"},{"time":571870,"text":"There's still time to change\nthe road you're on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576514,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":578733,"text":"Couldn't you just listen to that all day?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581368,"text":"All right, here it is backwards,"},{"time":582999,"text":"and see if you can hear the hidden\nmessages that are supposedly in there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587513,"text":"(Music with unintelligible lyrics)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601450,"text":"(Lyrics) Satan!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":602768,"text":"(Unintelligible lyrics continue)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":616934,"text":"What did you get?\nAudience: Satan!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":618578,"text":"Satan. OK, at least we got \"Satan\"."},{"time":620314,"text":"Now, I'll prime the auditory\npart of your brain"},{"time":622640,"text":"to tell you what you're supposed\nto hear, and then hear it again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626101,"text":"(Music with lyrics)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":652673,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":653783,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":655014,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661427,"text":"You can't miss it\nwhen I tell you what's there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":667274,"text":"I'm going to just end\nwith a positive, nice little story."},{"time":671333,"text":"The Skeptics is a nonprofit\neducational organization."},{"time":674202,"text":"We're always looking for little\ngood things that people do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677046,"text":"And in England, there's a pop singer."},{"time":679079,"text":"One of the top popular singers\nin England today, Katie Melua."},{"time":682848,"text":"And she wrote a beautiful song."},{"time":684400,"text":"It was in the top five in 2005, called,\n\"Nine Million Bicycles in Beijing.\""},{"time":690000,"text":"It's a love story -- she's sort\nof the Norah Jones of the UK --"},{"time":693120,"text":"about how she much loves her guy,"},{"time":694765,"text":"and compared to nine million\nbicycles, and so forth."},{"time":697265,"text":"And she has this one passage here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699514,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":700574,"text":"(Lyrics) We are 12 billion\nlight-years from the edge"}]},{"cues":[{"time":706369,"text":"That's a guess,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":708718,"text":"No one can ever say it's true,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":712453,"text":"But I know that I will always be with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717731,"text":"Michael Shermer: Well, that's nice.\nAt least she got it close."},{"time":720720,"text":"In America it'd be,\n\"We're 6,000 light years from the edge.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":723667,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":724727,"text":"But my friend, Simon Singh, the particle\nphysicist now turned science educator,"},{"time":728520,"text":"who wrote the book\n\"The Big Bang,\" and so on,"},{"time":730671,"text":"uses every chance he gets\nto promote good science."},{"time":733100,"text":"And so he wrote an op-ed piece\nin \"The Guardian\" about Katie's song,"},{"time":736410,"text":"in which he said, well, we know exactly\nhow far from the edge."},{"time":741470,"text":"You know, it's 13.7 billion light years,\nand it's not a guess."},{"time":745312,"text":"We know within precise\nerror bars how close it is."},{"time":749600,"text":"So we can say, although not absolutely\ntrue, it's pretty close to being true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753434,"text":"And, to his credit, Katie called him up\nafter this op-ed piece came out, and said,"},{"time":758197,"text":"\"I'm so embarrassed.\nI was in the astronomy club."},{"time":760592,"text":"I should've known better.\""},{"time":761894,"text":"And she re-cut the song."},{"time":763140,"text":"So I will end with the new version."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765012,"text":"(Music with lyrics)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":766300,"text":"We are 13.7 billion light years"},{"time":768745,"text":"from the edge of the observable universe."},{"time":772260,"text":"That's a good estimate\nwith well-defined error bars."},{"time":776053,"text":"And with the available information,"},{"time":779229,"text":"I predict that I will always be with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783596,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":784777,"text":"How cool is that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":785969,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}